    {
      "name": "debug_withdraw_liquidity",
      "docs": [
        "Emergency-recovery withdraw without burning LP tokens.",
        "",
        "Always compiled into production builds — the admin-panel relies on",
        "this entrypoint for emergency drain. Originally gated behind the",
        "`debug-withdraw` cargo feature (audit FIX C-06); the gate was removed",
        "so the recovery path is guaranteed present in every deploy.",
        "",
        "### Authority",
        "- `collect_protocol_fees_authority` only.",
        "",
        "### Prerequisites",
        "- Pool MUST be disabled (`pool_enabled = false`) before calling —",
        "enforced inside the handler via `PoolMustBeDisabled`.",
        "",
        "### Parameters",
        "- `token_amounts` — per-token withdraw amounts (use `0` to skip)."
      ],
      "discriminator": [
        139,
        40,
        126,
        103,
        199,
        34,
        143,
        137
      ],
      "accounts": [
        {
          "name": "config"
        },
        {
          "name": "pool",
          "writable": true
        },
        {
          "name": "authority",
          "docs": [
            "Only collect_protocol_fees_authority (= Treasury PDA) can call this."
          ],
          "signer": true
        }
      ],
      "args": [
        {
          "name": "token_amounts",
          "type": {
            "vec": "u64"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "get_pool_info",
      "docs": [
        "Get all pool data (read-only view function)",
        "",
        "This instruction emits a PoolInfo event containing all pool state.",
        "Call with `simulate: true` to read data without modifying state.",
        "",
        "### Usage from TypeScript:",
        "```typescript",
        "const tx = await program.methods.getPoolInfo()",
        ".accounts({ pool: poolPubkey })",
        ".simulate();",
        "// Parse PoolInfo event from tx.events",
        "```"
      ],
